  "text": "Noise produced by TSHDs has been measured on a number of occasions, and in general reported sound levels appear higher than ones documented for CSDs. [CITATION_1] measured six TSHDs, stating that sound levels below 500 Hz were in line with those expected for a cargo ship travelling at modest speeds (8 -16 kn). The maximum broadband source SPL was 189.9 dB re 1 mPa at 1 metre (calculated based on 1/3 octave band levels from 31.6 Hz to 39.8 kHz, as reported by [CITATION_2] . Estimated 1/3 octave band source levels above 1 kHz were relatively high, which was probably a result of the coarse aggregate pumped through the dredge pipe. Using an identical approach, de Jong et al. (2012) found very similar results to [CITATION_3] , but 1/3 octave band source levels clearly showed a steady decline beyond 1 kHz. This was due to the material dredged (sand as opposed to gravel).",
